# GitHub Discussions Setup

## Required Categories

Configure at: `https://github.com/{owner}/{repo}/discussions/categories`

Click "New category" to add each category.

| Category | Icon | Format | Description |
|----------|------|--------|-------------|
| **ADR** | 📐 | Announcement | Architecture Decision Records - Design decisions |
| **Knowledge** | 💡 | Announcement | Technical knowledge and patterns - Confirmed solutions |
| **Research** | 🔬 | Open-ended | Research requests and findings - Discussion format |

> Session continuity is handled via `In progress` Issue body + comments (Issue 一元化), not Discussion category.

## Category Details

### ADR 📐

**Format**: Announcement (decisions are final)
**Purpose**: Record architecture decisions with context

**Title format**: `ADR-{NNN}: {decision title}`

**Body template**:
```markdown
## Status
{Proposed | Accepted | Deprecated | Superseded by ADR-XXX}

## Context
{What is the issue that we're seeing that is motivating this decision?}

## Decision
{What is the change that we're proposing and/or doing?}

## Consequences
{What becomes easier or more difficult because of this change?}

## Alternatives Considered
{Other options that were evaluated}
```

### Knowledge 💡

**Format**: Announcement (confirmed knowledge)
**Purpose**: Document patterns, solutions, and best practices

**Title format**: `{Topic or Pattern Name}`

**Body template**:
```markdown
## Problem
{What issue does this solve?}

## Solution
{The confirmed solution or pattern}

## Example
```{language}
{Code example}
```

## References
- Issue #{n} (where this was discovered)
- External docs: {URL}

## Related Rules
- `.claude/rules/{rule-name}.md`
```

### Research 🔬

**Format**: Open-ended (allows discussion)
**Purpose**: Investigation requests and findings

**Title format**: `[Research] {topic}`

**Body template**:
```markdown
## Question
{What needs to be researched?}

## Context
{Why is this research needed?}

## Scope
- {Specific aspect 1}
- {Specific aspect 2}

## Findings
{Updated as research progresses}

## Conclusion
{Final recommendation or decision}

## Next Steps
- [ ] Create ADR if decision needed
- [ ] Create Knowledge if pattern confirmed
- [ ] Create Issue if action needed
```

## Usage Flow

```
Research (investigation)
    ↓
ADR (if decision needed)
    ↓
Knowledge (confirmed pattern)
    ↓
.claude/rules/ (AI-readable extract)
```

## Integration with Issues/Projects

Discussions can be added to Projects:
```bash
gh project item-add PROJECT_ID --url DISCUSSION_URL
```

Cross-reference in Issues:
```markdown
See Discussion #30 for background research.
```

## Notes

- Discussions use same number space as Issues (#1, #2, ...)
- Cross-references work: "See #30" links to Discussion or Issue
- Projects can track both Issues and Discussions
